Pernambuco Championship 1943

Source: "Campeonato Pernambucano - 1915 a 1970", book written by 
Carlos Celso Cordeiro and Luciano Guedes Cordeiro.
Primeiro Turno
04/04/43 Sport Recife 4-2 América-PE
08/04/43 Náutico 8-0 Flamengo (RE)
11/04/43 Great Western 3-2 Santa Cruz
15/04/43 Sport Recife 6-0 Flamengo (RE)
18/04/43 Náutico 3-2 América-PE
22/04/43 Sport Recife 3-1 Great Western
25/04/43 Santa Cruz 7-0 Flamengo (RE)
29/04/43 América-PE 1-1 Great Western
02/05/43 Santa Cruz 2-2 Náutico
06/05/43 Great Western 5-1 Flamengo (RE)
09/05/43 Náutico 1-0 Sport Recife
13/05/43 América-PE 10-3 Flamengo (RE)
16/05/43 Sport Recife 3-0 Santa Cruz
20/05/43 Náutico 6-1 Great Western
25/05/43 Santa Cruz 3-1 América-PE
                          P   G   W   D   L  GF  GA  GD
 1. Náutico               9   5   4   1   0  20   5  15
--------------------------------------------------------
 2. Sport Recife          8   5   4   0   1  16   4  12  to Final
--------------------------------------------------------
 3. Santa Cruz            5   5   2   1   2  14   9   5
 4. Great Western         5   5   2   1   2  11  13  -2
 5. América-PE            3   5   1   1   3  16  14   2
 6. Flamengo (RE)         0   5   0   0   5   4  36 -32
Obs. Náutico abandoned the competition. Due to this, the title of
Primeiro Turno and the berth to Final were awarded to Sport.
Segundo Turno
30/05/43        Sport Recife 4-1 Great Western
06/06/43        Santa Cruz 5-3 Flamengo (RE)
13/06/43        América-PE 1-1 Sport Recife
20/06/43        Santa Cruz 2-0 Great Western
27/06/43        América-PE 5-1 Flamengo (RE)
04/07/43        Sport Recife 3-0 Santa Cruz
18/07/43        América-PE 3-0 Great Western
                          P   G   W   D   L  GF  GA  GD
 1. América-PE            5   3   2   1   0   9   2   7
 2. Sport Recife          5   3   2   1   0   8   2   6
 3. Santa Cruz            4   3   2   0   1   7   6   1
 4. Flamengo (RE)         0   2   0   0   2   4  10  -6
 5. Great Western         0   3   0   0   3   1   9  -8
Obs. The championship was interrupted and the no team was
awarded the title of Segundo Turno.

Sport was declared state champions of 1943 due to had won the Primeiro
Turno.
